[Name] LXC
[Summary] LXC is a userspace interface for the Linux kernel containment features
[Description] LXC (Linux Containers) is an operating-system-level virtualization method
for running multiple isolated Linux systems (containers) on a control host using a single
Linux kernel.
[License] GNU Lesser General Public License 2.1
[Homepage] https://linuxcontainers.org/lxc
